00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:08.296
And this is the distribution
of River Blindness,

00:02:08.296 --> 00:02:09.045
or Onchocerciasis.

00:02:12.390 --> 00:02:14.990
And this is where
The Carter Center

00:02:14.990 --> 00:02:17.800
involved in combating
this disease.

00:02:17.800 --> 00:02:20.480
In fact, in the
Western hemisphere,

00:02:20.480 --> 00:02:22.880
we are left with
this small place.

00:02:22.880 --> 00:02:29.280
Actually, not a small place,
but few people, in the Amazon.

00:02:29.280 --> 00:02:34.310
Largely the Yanomami--
between Venezuela and Brazil.

00:02:34.310 --> 00:02:36.830
This is how the
disease presents.

00:02:36.830 --> 00:02:40.400
This is a young
man, 13 years old.

00:02:40.400 --> 00:02:44.220
And you can see on this
side of the-- of the leg,

00:02:44.220 --> 00:02:49.420
this is where the
worms are in the leg.

00:02:49.420 --> 00:02:51.610
And he's scratching
on that side.

00:02:51.610 --> 00:02:56.690
When the worms die, they
cause an immune reaction.

00:02:56.690 --> 00:03:00.710
And he has more of these worms
on this side of the body,

00:03:00.710 --> 00:03:03.900
and so he's scratching
and creating

00:03:03.900 --> 00:03:07.240
secondary infections
that are causing this.

00:03:07.240 --> 00:03:11.510
And this is a nodule where the
female and the male worm live.

00:03:11.510 --> 00:03:14.390
The female produces
thousands of baby worms.

00:03:14.390 --> 00:03:17.140
This is in nematode worm.

00:03:17.140 --> 00:03:19.780
This is called leopard skin.

00:03:19.780 --> 00:03:23.120
If you go and find someone
who was not burnt in fire,

00:03:23.120 --> 00:03:25.080
or something like
that, and he has

00:03:25.080 --> 00:03:30.220
this kind of white skin,
which we call leopard skin,

00:03:30.220 --> 00:03:33.140
that's Onchocerciasis.

00:03:33.140 --> 00:03:36.460
And this called-- we
call this hanging groins.

00:03:36.460 --> 00:03:39.870
But you can see how the
skin looks very rough.

00:03:39.870 --> 00:03:43.390
We even call it elephant skin.

00:03:43.390 --> 00:03:48.560
And River Blindness can cause
these terrible hydroceles.

00:03:48.560 --> 00:03:50.350
A [INAUDIBLE], for
instance does it,

00:03:50.350 --> 00:03:53.520
but-- or so, this
disease causes it.

00:03:53.520 --> 00:03:57.690
And of course, you become blind.

00:03:57.690 --> 00:04:02.100
And a patient with
River Blindness--

00:04:02.100 --> 00:04:03.510
when they are
getting blind, they

00:04:03.510 --> 00:04:05.090
see as if they are in a tunnel.

00:04:05.090 --> 00:04:07.260
They have what we
call tunnel vision.

00:04:07.260 --> 00:04:11.780
And this is the only disease
that causes this tunnel vision

00:04:11.780 --> 00:04:15.190
before, of course,
you get blind.

00:04:15.190 --> 00:04:18.126
And it has, also, complications.

00:04:18.126 --> 00:04:22.079
And there's a competition
called Nakalanga Syndrome.

00:04:22.079 --> 00:04:24.000
This is dwarfism.

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:29.790
And this guy's 28 years old,
and this, also-- this guy's

00:04:29.790 --> 00:04:31.490
28 years old.

00:04:31.490 --> 00:04:33.310
And the difference
between this, is

00:04:33.310 --> 00:04:35.330
that this one has never grown.

00:04:35.330 --> 00:04:36.200
He's a child.

00:04:36.200 --> 00:04:39.240
He has never developed secondary
sexual characteristics,

00:04:39.240 --> 00:04:41.610
so he'll never marry,
he'll never have a kid,

00:04:41.610 --> 00:04:46.900
he's actually a child with no
pubic hair-- nothing like that.

00:04:46.900 --> 00:04:52.490
And then, this disease
can also cause epilepsy.

00:04:52.490 --> 00:04:58.450
And the extreme seizures,
recently mentioned

00:04:58.450 --> 00:04:59.780
called, Nodding Disease.

00:04:59.780 --> 00:05:02.560
If you Google
Nodding Disease, you

00:05:02.560 --> 00:05:05.450
will see how terrible it can be.

00:05:05.450 --> 00:05:08.780
We don't know whether it's
associated with this disease,

00:05:08.780 --> 00:05:11.500
but some people
already believe that it

00:05:11.500 --> 00:05:14.620
is associated with
River Blindness.

00:05:14.620 --> 00:05:21.560
And this is 99-- over 99
of the cases are in Africa.

00:05:21.560 --> 00:05:26.800
And this is former
Onchocerciasis Control Program,

00:05:26.800 --> 00:05:33.550
that was initiated in
1974, and closed 20-- 2002.

00:05:33.550 --> 00:05:35.710
And this is the African
program for them.

00:05:35.710 --> 00:05:40.320
Onchocerciasis Control
that was initiated in '97,

00:05:40.320 --> 00:05:45.050
and is expected close in 2025.

00:05:45.050 --> 00:05:47.190
And these are the countries
that Carter Center

00:05:47.190 --> 00:05:49.940
has-- is assisting.

00:05:49.940 --> 00:05:52.960
And they have launched-- instead
of controlling the disease,

00:05:52.960 --> 00:05:55.085
they are out to eliminate
the disease where

00:05:55.085 --> 00:05:57.150
it can be found in
these countries.

00:05:57.150 --> 00:06:01.860
Uganda is at the forefront of
Onchocerciasis elimination,

00:06:01.860 --> 00:06:03.690
or River Blindness elimination.

00:06:03.690 --> 00:06:06.700
We've got 3.5 million
at risk, Sudan--

00:06:06.700 --> 00:06:11.050
about this-- that is Sudan
North, Ethiopia-- at least 31

00:06:11.050 --> 00:06:12.980
million people at the risk.

00:06:12.980 --> 00:06:16.970
We know that the mapping is not
complete as I will show you.

00:06:16.970 --> 00:06:21.390
Nigeria-- 37.4, the
America's, of course,

00:06:21.390 --> 00:06:24.890
we are almost finishing
the job there.

00:06:24.890 --> 00:06:30.780
But I'll be showing you
where we need Google.

00:06:30.780 --> 00:06:36.710
We use a tablet called
Ivermectin, provided my Merck

00:06:36.710 --> 00:06:38.640
Company.

00:06:38.640 --> 00:06:41.790
It's donated free as long
as it is it required,

00:06:41.790 --> 00:06:44.680
and as much as needed.

00:06:44.680 --> 00:06:48.470
And so when you give
it to once a year--

00:06:48.470 --> 00:06:51.280
a one dose a year
per person, you

00:06:51.280 --> 00:06:52.630
are controlling the disease.

00:06:52.630 --> 00:06:54.400
You are not stopping
transmission.

00:06:54.400 --> 00:06:59.060
But when you give it twice,
you are after transmission.

00:06:59.060 --> 00:07:00.860
You want to control
transmission,

00:07:00.860 --> 00:07:03.960
and the worms in someone's body.

00:07:03.960 --> 00:07:07.400
But if you are doing vector
control, or vector elimination

00:07:07.400 --> 00:07:11.760
with a-- by a biodegradable
agent called, Temephos,

00:07:11.760 --> 00:07:15.080
you finish the job faster.

00:07:15.080 --> 00:07:19.140
Twice a year with a tablet--
you take six to seven years.

00:07:19.140 --> 00:07:22.210
But with the vector
control, you probably

00:07:22.210 --> 00:07:24.080
bring it down to three years.

00:07:24.080 --> 00:07:26.620
Or two years to
control transmission.

00:07:26.620 --> 00:07:28.710
And then you can
continue treating

00:07:28.710 --> 00:07:30.200
for the next, maybe, two years.

00:07:30.200 --> 00:07:32.790
And then you are done
with-- we are done.

00:07:32.790 --> 00:07:36.050
And this is how these worms
look like in the body--

00:07:36.050 --> 00:07:37.280
in someone's body.

00:07:37.280 --> 00:07:45.300
The female worm is very long,
and lives for ten to 12 years.

00:07:45.300 --> 00:07:47.600
Now, if you have
all these people,

00:07:47.600 --> 00:07:50.730
and you take them to
health facilities--

00:07:50.730 --> 00:07:54.365
medical facilities, the medical
facilities will get clogged

00:07:54.365 --> 00:07:56.610
and will shut down.

00:07:56.610 --> 00:08:02.340
So what we do is treat people--
train people, and treat them

00:08:02.340 --> 00:08:03.450
within their communities.

00:08:03.450 --> 00:08:06.340
So they learn how to do it.

00:08:06.340 --> 00:08:09.610
They determine the
dosage, they record,

00:08:09.610 --> 00:08:14.120
we provide the medicine, they
treat, and take the records

00:08:14.120 --> 00:08:15.050
back to health units.

00:08:15.050 --> 00:08:17.220
And through the health
units, we get reports.

00:08:17.220 --> 00:08:19.950
And order for more tablets.

00:08:19.950 --> 00:08:26.020
And-- so this is
a teacher training

00:08:26.020 --> 00:08:28.850
people in the community
under Mango tree.

00:08:28.850 --> 00:08:30.500
That's the way it should be.

00:08:30.500 --> 00:08:32.470
And that's where they
should be treated from.

00:08:32.470 --> 00:08:35.059
And we don't even use
scales, like in the hospital,

00:08:35.059 --> 00:08:36.630
to determine dosage.

00:08:36.630 --> 00:08:40.409
We use a stick as a
surrogate for weight-- height

00:08:40.409 --> 00:08:41.750
as a surrogate for weight.

00:08:41.750 --> 00:08:44.920
And doing research, we
realized that we could actually

00:08:44.920 --> 00:08:47.200
let weight by height.

00:08:47.200 --> 00:08:51.550
And so using any stick
calibrated will do.

00:08:51.550 --> 00:08:53.900
And we don't have
to pay for that.

00:08:53.900 --> 00:08:56.070
Again, when you come to
these local communities--

00:08:56.070 --> 00:08:58.250
their neighborhoods,
you discover

00:08:58.250 --> 00:09:01.100
that women get involved
and become very active.

00:09:01.100 --> 00:09:07.040
And so this is the stick at not
cost-- was got from the bush.

00:09:07.040 --> 00:09:10.840
We helped-- the supervisor
helped to calibrate it,

00:09:10.840 --> 00:09:12.970
he's also a village person.

00:09:12.970 --> 00:09:16.950
And they are treating
their own community.

00:09:16.950 --> 00:09:21.200
This is river
gauging to determine

00:09:21.200 --> 00:09:23.880
the amount of chemical
you can put in the river

00:09:23.880 --> 00:09:27.075
to clean the larval
stages of the black fly.

00:09:27.075 --> 00:09:28.450
I'll be showing
you the black fly

00:09:28.450 --> 00:09:31.060
is a vector for this nematode.

00:09:31.060 --> 00:09:33.690
And this is how
they are using it.

00:09:33.690 --> 00:09:34.600
We don't need planes.

00:09:34.600 --> 00:09:37.940
Like, in the 70's, they
used planes, in West Africa,

00:09:37.940 --> 00:09:41.550
to dose rivers with
this a bit, but now we

00:09:41.550 --> 00:09:44.850
use knapsacks sprayers,
train the villagers,

00:09:44.850 --> 00:09:47.810
and they do it-- show
them how to do it.

00:09:47.810 --> 00:09:50.980
This is how beautiful
an environment where

00:09:50.980 --> 00:09:53.210
Onchocerciasis, or River
Blindness looks like.

00:09:53.210 --> 00:09:56.420
You are all invited
to come and visit.

00:09:56.420 --> 00:09:59.630
Especially, where
there's no transmission.

00:09:59.630 --> 00:10:01.640
It's beautiful country.

00:10:01.640 --> 00:10:06.350
And this is called Simulium
damnosum, a damn nuisance.

00:10:06.350 --> 00:10:10.030
It bites like a bulldog.

00:10:10.030 --> 00:10:16.620
And as it tears your
body, the nematode worm

00:10:16.620 --> 00:10:19.040
gets inside your body.

00:10:19.040 --> 00:10:22.450
And this is how it looks like.

00:10:22.450 --> 00:10:27.500
The larval stages, and
when the debris, and what,

00:10:27.500 --> 00:10:28.580
in the rivers.

00:10:28.580 --> 00:10:31.640
And you can even see
the flies flying off.

00:10:31.640 --> 00:10:35.630
It needs a crab in
it's life cycle--

00:10:35.630 --> 00:10:37.990
to complete the life cycle.

00:10:37.990 --> 00:10:40.740
I'm showing you these
flies because they

00:10:40.740 --> 00:10:43.460
are vectors for the disease.

00:10:43.460 --> 00:10:45.250
And this is how you trap crab.

00:10:45.250 --> 00:10:51.860
This is a crab trapping device--
locally made by communities.

00:10:51.860 --> 00:10:55.050
Actually, you trap
mud fish with this.

00:10:55.050 --> 00:10:57.170
And now they have adapted
it to trapping crabs.

00:10:57.170 --> 00:11:00.100
And they use them
to monitor where

00:11:00.100 --> 00:11:02.000
the transmission has
been interrupted.

00:11:02.000 --> 00:11:07.800
If they are clean then we know
there's no flies breeding.

00:11:07.800 --> 00:11:13.740
This is Uganda, and the
control, from 1992 to 2007.

00:11:13.740 --> 00:11:17.220
And Ugandans failed to know--
we must do something else.

00:11:17.220 --> 00:11:20.540
We cannot continue
treating endlessly.

00:11:20.540 --> 00:11:24.260
And in 2007, they launched
elimination as a policy

00:11:24.260 --> 00:11:25.510
for the country.

00:11:25.510 --> 00:11:30.220
And see where we are-- all
these places are clean.

